The paper deals with the problem of secure communication in networks with an eavesdropper, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses network topology and communication demands, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions network coding, which is a technique used in distributed computing (cs.CC).
